Male. Antenna (Figs 1, 9) short, not extending to middle of elytra, antennomere II short, subequal to V– VII in length, antennomere III long, 2 times as long as antennomere II, antennomere IV slightly shorter than III, slightly longer than V, antnnomeres V–VII widened apically, antennomere VIII strongly swollen, about 2.5 times as long as III, antennomere IX (Fig. 15 ) articulated towards mesal edge on apex of VIII, cylindrical but laterally twisted at base, glabrous area oblong, from apical 1 / 3 extending near base, antennomere X subequal to IX, antennomere XI longest, about 1.3 times as long as X. Front and middle tarsomere I relatively wider and shorter than females. Abdominal ventrite V (Fig. 18 ) trilobed, apex of median lobe truncate, apices of lateral lobes obliquely truncate, base of median lobe concave. Genitalia (
Fig. 22
) asymmetric, with a erected process behind base of gonopore, apically pointed and directed downwards; apex rounded and slightly emarginated towards left; endophallus with apical spiculae projected from base of gonopore, slender and curved inwards, horn-like; median and basal spiculae slender and laterally flattened.
